cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the task of lesion matching in mammography images using deep learning. The use of a patch-based Siamese network also suggests that it could fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also involves the analysis of large datasets, which could place it under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the evaluation of the matching network in a full detection pipeline suggests that it could also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
